    "bias",
    "prediction"
  ],
  "snippet": "import numpy as np\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt",
  "cells": [
    {
      "kind": "markdown",
      "source": "## \ud83d\udce6 Import Libraries\n\nWe are importing tools that help us work with data and graphs.\n\n- `numpy` helps us handle numbers and calculations  \n- `matplotlib` helps us draw graphs  \n\nThink of these as tools we need before starting."
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "source": "import numpy as np\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt",
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "kind": "markdown",
      "source": "## \ud83d\udcca Create Data (Input and Output)\n\nHere we are creating our dataset.\n\n- `X` = input data (experience and skills)  \n- `y` = output (salary)\n\nEach row represents one person.\n\nExample: [1, 2] means  \n1 year experience and 2 skill level."
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "source": "# Features: [experience, skills]\nX = np.array([\n    [1, 2],\n    [2, 3],\n    [3, 4],\n    [4, 5]\n])\n\n# Salary (output)\ny = np.array([15, 25, 35, 45])",
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "kind": "markdown",
      "source": "## \u2699\ufe0f Initialize Weights and Bias\n\nWe start with some simple values.\n\n- `w` = weights \u2192 how important each input is  \n- `b` = bias \u2192 base value (starting point)\n\nRight now, these are just guesses.  \nThe model will improve them while learning."
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "source": "w = np.array([1, 1])\nb = 0",
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "kind": "markdown",
      "source": "## \ud83d\udd01 Train the Model\n\nThis is where learning happens.\n\nThe model:\n1. Makes predictions  \n2. Checks how wrong it is (error)  \n3. Updates weights and bias  \n\nIt repeats this many times to get better results."
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "source": "learning_rate = 0.01\nepochs = 1000\n\nfor i in range(epochs):\n    predictions = np.dot(X, w) + b\n    error = predictions - y\n\n    w = w - learning_rate * np.dot(X.T, error) / len(X)\n    b = b - learning_rate * np.sum(error) / len(X)",
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "kind": "markdown",
      "source": "## \ud83d\udd0d Check Learned Values\n\nAfter training, we print:\n\n- Final weights (`w`)  \n- Final bias (`b`)  \n\nThese are the learned values that help the model make predictions."
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "source": "print(\"Weights:\", w)\nprint(\"Bias:\", b)",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": "Weights: [4.85676843 5.0553241 ]\nBias: 0.19855566252877405"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "markdown",
      "source": "## \ud83d\udcc8 Plot the Graph\n\nNow we visualize the results.\n\n- Points = actual salary (real data)  \n- Line = predicted salary (model output)\n\nIf the line is close to the points,  \nit means our model is working well."
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "source": "predictions = np.dot(X, w) + b\n\nexperience = X[:, 0]\n\nplt.scatter(experience, y, label=\"Actual Salary\")\nplt.plot(experience, predictions, label=\"Predicted Salary\")\n\nplt.xlabel(\"Experience\")\nplt.ylabel(\"Salary\")\nplt.title(\"Experience vs Salary (Integer Example)\")\nplt.legend()\n\nplt.show()",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "image",
          "content": ""
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
